modules.description: This module provides operations for parsing and managing command-line configuration parameters, including value conversion, metadata-driven parameter declaration (e.g., deprecation, defaults, documentation), and manpage generation. It works with scalar types (bool, int, float, string), structured types (lists, arrays, tuples), and path-based values, supporting flexible separator-driven parsing and optional/custom validation rules. It is used to build type-safe, self-documenting command-line interfaces with rich metadata handling.

This module handles command-line argument parsing, logging at various severity levels, and progress tracking for long-running tasks like disassembly or symbolic execution. It supports typed configuration parameters with metadata, automatic documentation, and validation, working with scalars, lists, and path-based values. You can define type-safe command-line interfaces, log diagnostic messages with format strings, and report progress with status updates. Specific uses include configuring analysis settings, emitting debug or error messages, and monitoring multi-stage processing pipelines.
